  "prompt": "Is there any backup plan after failing in UPSC exam?",
  "response": "If you fail in the UPSC (Union Public Service Commission) exam, there are several alternative career paths and backup plans:\n\n1. Retry UPSC Exam\n- Prepare again with more focused strategy\n- Learn from previous attempt's mistakes\n- Can appear multiple times until age limit\n\n2. State Public Service Commission (SPSC)\n- Similar exam pattern\n- State-level administrative services\n- Relatively less competitive\n\n3. Banking Exams\n- IBPS PO\n- SBI PO\n- RBI Grade B\n- Offer good salary and stability\n\n4. Staff Selection Commission (SSC)\n- CGL (Combined Graduate Level)\n- CHSL (Combined Higher Secondary Level)\n- Offer government job opportunities\n\n5. Defense Services\n- NDA\n- CDS (Combined Defense Services)\n- Army recruitment exams\n\n6. Other Government Competitive Exams\n- Railways\n- Insurance sector\n- Public sector undertakings\n\n7. Private Sector Opportunities\n- Management roles\n- Corporate jobs\n- MNCs\n- Consulting firms\n\n8. Higher Education\n- MBA\n- Additional qualifications\n- Specialized courses\n\n9. Teaching/Academic Career\n- School/college teaching\n- Research positions\n- Academic administrative roles\n\nEach option offers different opportunities and requires specific preparation strategies.",
